long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1215681 Fedora version of veusz
Description of problem:
veusz distributed with Fedora does not display tab graphics correctly. Two figures attached: 1) the binary distribution from veusz web site and 2) veusz from the standard fedora 25 repo.
Created attachment 1215682 veusz from web site
Look at the left bottom corner and you can see that the tab graphical labels are missing in the fedora version.

This appears to be a bug in the theme GNOME uses for qt4 applications.
To work around this, you can install the qt-config package and run qtconfig-qt4 and choose a different qt theme.
I think the appropriate component to file this bug is in adwaita-qt4. I suggest you move this bug there.
Yes, I confirm that this is the issue. Thanks!!
Sorry, I couldn't see adwaita-qt4 componnent & how do I change this to that?
